@@TJvFormMagnet.Active
Description:
if this property is true, the magnet is active. if this property is false, the form will act completly normally.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormMagnet.Area
Description:
This property is the distance in pixel from which the form is magnetized (either for the screen or the main form).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormMagnet.FormGlue
Description:
if this property is true, all other form's scotched on the form will follow the form in his movements. (Pay attention not to set this property to true in more than a form, or you won't be able to separate them).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormMagnet.MainFormMagnet
Description:
if this property is true, the form will be magnetized by the main form. (if the form is the main form, it has no effect).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFormMagnet.ScreenMagnet
Description:
if this property is true (and the active property too), the form will be attired by the borders of the screen. if your form is too near from a border, it will automatically scotch to it.

